## IMPORTANT finding (not a bug — must be recorded): post-hoc filter != live child
The slicer estimated -0.082R by FILTERING the parent's already-realized 3573 trades
to the 893 where ADX<=q30. The live child will NOT reproduce that. When the child
skips an ADX-blocked signal, `signal_pos` advances by 1, so the child is then free to
enter on later bars the parent skipped while it was mid-trade. So the child's trade
SET is not "parent trades minus filtered" — it can contain new trades the parent
never took. Consequence: the validation realized-R will differ from the -0.082
discovery estimate, by design. This is exactly the gap validation exists to expose.
Record it explicitly (KNOWN_LIMITATIONS or the validation doc) so the divergence is
not misread as a bug. This applies to the slicer methodology generally, not just
this child.

